SIMPLE: pax
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pax
<hw>Pax</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pax</ets> peace.
See <er>Peace</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The kiss
of peace; also, the embrace in the sanctuary now substituted for it at
High Mass in Roman Catholic churches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A tablet or board, on which
is a representation of Christ, of the Virgin Mary, or of some saint and
which, in the Mass, was kissed by the priest and then by the people, in
medi⟦ae⟧val times; an osculatory. It is still used in communities,
confraternities, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Kiss the <qex>pax</qex>, and be quiet like your neighbors.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Friendship, or a friend; -- esp. in the phrases
<xex>to make pax with</xex>, to make friends with, <xex>to be good
pax</xex>, to be good friends; also, truce; -- used esp.
interjectionally.</def> <mark>[Eng. Schoolboy Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paxillose</ent>⟦br⟧
